{
  "doc_id": "8781",
  "text": "In situ hybridization was performed as described previously [CITATION_1] with some modification. Excised hindguts isolated from 10 termites were placed into a 1.5-ml microfuge tube along with 100 μl of solution U and disrupted by plastic pestle on ice. The resulting suspension was then filtered through a 100-μm pore size nylon mesh to remove the gut debris.",
